Despite losing its outright majority, the PS remains a significant force in Portuguese politics. As the second-largest party in the parliament, it will likely play a key role in forming the next government and shaping the country's political agenda for the coming years.

The party's loss of its absolute majority in 2024 may be seen as a shift in voter sentiment, with some Portuguese citizens seeking a change from the previous PS-led government. However, the party's enduring popularity and its ability to form coalitions with other left-leaning parties suggest that it will continue to be a major player in Portuguese politics.

Overall, the Socialist Party (PS) remains a central force in the Portuguese political landscape, with its leader Pedro Nuno Santos and its center-left platform continuing to influence the country's political direction.</data>
